[[File:Debris disk AU Mic HST.jpg|thumb|A debris disk around the star [[AU Microscopii]]. The black circle in the center is an occulting disk of a coronagraph.]] An '''occulting disk''' is a small disk used in a [[telescope]] to block the view of a bright object in order to allow observation of a fainter one. The [[coronagraph]], at its simplest, is an occulting disk in the focal plane of a [[telescope]], or in front of the entrance [[aperture]], that blocks out the image of the solar disk, so that the [[corona]] can be seen. [[Starshade]] is one designed to fly in formation with a [[space telescope]] to image [[exoplanet]]s.
